definition: right/correct/couple/pair/towards/at/for/to face/opposite/to treat (sb a certain way)/to match together/to adjust/to fit/to suit/to answer/to reply/classifier: couple
see 驢唇不對馬嘴|驴唇不对马嘴[lu:2 chun2 bu4 dui4 ma3 zui3]
pinyin: niu2 tou2 bu4 dui4 ma3 zui3

definition: lit. a donkey's lips do not match a horse's mouth (idiom)/fig. beside the point/incongruous
pinyin: lu:2 chun2 bu4 dui4 ma3 zui3

definition: erhua variant of 不對勁|不对劲[bu4 dui4 jin4]
(of a person) objectionable/(of two people) to find each other disagreeable
not proper/not fit for the occasion
right or wrong?/Is it right?/OK, yes? (colloquial)

sentences.english: Something’s not right here, I thought.
sentences.chinese: 我想事情有些不对头的地方。

sentences.english: In that market the asymmetry in risk/reward works in the opposite way to stocks.
sentences.chinese: 在这个市场上，风险回报的不对称性正好与股市相反。

sentences.english: The soup that I ordered yesterday did not taste as it should.
sentences.chinese: 昨天我叫的汤，味道好像不对劲。

sentences.english: But there seems something wrong in the rugby this year.
sentences.chinese: 但是今年的橄榄球赛好象有点不对劲。

sentences.english: I could sense that there was something wrong. It felt wrong.
sentences.chinese: 我能感觉出一些不对，它不对劲。

sentences.english: But when things go wrong, they cannot adapt their tactics.
sentences.chinese: 不过当事情不对头的时候，他们不会改变策略。

sentences.english: They are sensitive to these issues because they know when it does not smell right , does not feel right, " says Zogby."
sentences.chinese: 他们对这些问题敏感，因为他们知道事情不对头。

sentences.english: During the memorial sequence, my son figured out something was wrong.
sentences.chinese: 放那个悼念的连续镜头时，我儿子觉出了有些不对头。

sentences.english: But in the past decade, something went horribly wrong.
sentences.chinese: 但在过去十年，事情变得不对劲了。

sentences.english: Once we started questioning her, things didn’t add up.
sentences.chinese: 一旦我们开始询问她，就发现事情不对劲了。

sentences.english: Nothing smells a rat. I told you that he's an all-right guy.
sentences.chinese: 没什么不对劲的，我告诉你他是一个很好的小伙子。

sentences.english: He quickly ran home, looking as if there was something wrong with him.
sentences.chinese: 他快步跑回家，看上去好象有什么事不对劲。

sentences.english: I don’t want to say he steals them, but I really smell a rat.
sentences.chinese: 虽然我不想说他偷我的书，但我确实觉得不对劲。

sentences.english: If you feel weird about something tell him.
sentences.chinese: 如果你感到有些事情不对劲，那就跟他直说。

sentences.english: This article is to analyze the influencing factor of apparent information asymmetry in medical dispute game.
sentences.chinese: 探讨医疗纠纷博弈表观信息不对称性的影响因素。

sentences.english: His remarks about gardening were hardly to the purpose.
sentences.chinese: 他对园艺的一席话简直是文不对题。

definition: right or wrong?/Is it right?/OK, yes? (colloquial)
mistake/wrong/bad/interlocking/complex/to grind/to polish/to alternate/to stagger/to miss/to let slip/to evade/to inlay with gold or silver
Correct!/Oh, that's right, ... (when one suddenly remembers sth one wanted to mention)/Oh, by the way, ...
unworthy/to let down/I'm sorry/excuse me/pardon me/if you please/sorry? (please repeat)
